  "prompt": "Is Xiaomi Redmi Note 3 up gradable to Marshmallow?",
  "response": "Yes, the Xiaomi Redmi Note 3 can be upgraded to **Android 6.0 Marshmallow**. The device originally launched with **Android 5.1 Lollipop** but Xiaomi provided an official update to Marshmallow via MI Cabinet, which is Xiaomi's custom Android-based operating system.\n\nTo upgrade your Redmi Note 3 to Marshmallow:\n\n1. Go to **Settings**.\n2. Select **About Phone**.\n3. Tap on **System Update** to check for the latest updates.\n4. Download and install the Marshmallow update if available.\n\nKeep in mind that the availability of the update might depend on your region and device variant. If the official update is no longer available, you might need to consider custom ROMs, but this requires unlocking the bootloader and flashing a custom recovery, which can void your warranty and carry risks.\n\nAlways back up your data before performing any updates or modifications to your device.",
